list.name: Default
list.comment: Added scrolling, and finding late units from a date functionality A new Menu item "Find late" was added. The user can now find units from inputting a specific date which they will be considered late. Also, minor improvements on the code.

task.summary: RentDVDDialog fully proofed and improved Added input checking methods to make sure the user enters the correct data, if one of the information is incorrect, the Dialog won't disappear.

Dialogs input checked thoroughly, Game & GameRentDialog classes are complete. The input of the user is thoroughly checked from the Dialog class to make sure the user enters the correct info. Game & RentGameDialog were completed and implemented into the program. The user can save the list as text now. Also, when returning a unit, the cost will appear on a popup and the unit will be removed from the list.

Error checking improved When returning a unit, the user CANNOT enter an empty date, a date before the unit was rented, or an invalid date as if the day value was bigger than 31 or less than 1 or the month value was bigger than 12. Plus minor fixing in some classes.

Added scrolling, and finding late units from a date functionality A new Menu item "Find late" was added. The user can now find units from inputting a specific date which they will be considered late. Also, minor improvements on the code.
Fixed a bug in findLate method In findLate method, the days late value was an int which was returning negative value, it is changed to a long.

Leading white space checked and removed. Minor bug improvements. The program checks if the user entered any leading white space and removes it using recursion. returning units needed a minor fixing. Also, the user can't enter a negative year when renting. And if the user enters an invalid date when returning or finding late unit, the date input popup will appear again after the error message.
If else statement in input check fixed.
Decreased instance variables and methods. Some instance variables can be converted to local variables, and that helped decrease some methods in the DVD and Dialog class.
